{0 SpecV2 Rocq Development}

This documentation mirrors the structure of the paper
{i A Semantic Reduction from Conditional Safety to Local Proofs}.

{1 Roadmap}

{2 Semantic Core}

- {!module-SpecV2.ReactiveModel} defines reactive programs and their concrete
  executions.
- {!module-SpecV2.ConditionalSafety} defines safety automata, conditional
  specifications, and the semantic predicates [AvoidA] and [AvoidG].
- {!module-SpecV2.ExplicitProduct} defines the explicit product and dangerous
  product steps.

{2 Local Proof Layer}

- {!module-SpecV2.GeneratedClauses} defines the semantic clauses extracted from
  the product.
- {!module-SpecV2.RelationalTriples} packages these clauses into relational
  Hoare triples over ticks.

{2 Meta-Theory}

- {!module-SpecV2.Soundness} proves the main soundness theorem.
- {!module-SpecV2.RelativeCompleteness} proves the relative-completeness
  directions.

{2 Concrete Example}

- {!module-SpecV2.ResettableDelayExample} instantiates the framework on the
  resettable-delay running example.

{1 Thematic Pages}

- {!page-model Overview of the semantic model}
- {!page-reduction Overview of generated clauses and triples}
- {!page-metatheory Overview of the main proofs}
- {!page-example Overview of the concrete instantiation}
